Class IdeCodeListener

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.eclipse.core.commands.IExecutionListener, org.eclipse.core.commands.IExecutionListenerWithChecks, org.eclipse.jface.text.IDocumentListener, org.eclipse.ui.IWorkbenchListener, Listener, CommandExecutionListener, DocumentListener, TextSelectionListener, WorkbenchListener, Registrable

    public final class IdeCodeListener
extends IdeListener
implements CommandExecutionListener, DocumentListener, TextSelectionListener, WorkbenchListener
    A listener of IDE code events. This listener handles desired events and eventually builds corresponding data transfer objects of type IdeCodeEventRequest and passes them to the UacaProxy to be transferred into the User Activity Central Application for further processing.

    Code operation types that this listener is interested in are determined by the IdeCodeEventType enumeration:

    • Copy - a code is copied.
    • Cut - a code is cut.
    • Paste - a code is pasted.
    • Selection changed - a code is selected, cursor is moved discarding current selection or the code selection is changed otherwise.

    Data available in an IdeCodeEventRequest:

    • code - related code.
    • document - related document, see documentation of IdeDocumentDto in IdeDocumentListener for more details.
    • endColumnIndex - zero based end position of code on document line.
    • endRowIndex - zero based end line number of code in document.
    • startColumnIndex - zero based start position of code on document line.
    • startRowIndex - zero based start line number of code in document.
    • See IdeListener for documentation of inherited data.

    Note that row and column offsets in documents start from zero instead of one.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Pavol Zbell
